==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Echidna
<hw>E*chid"na</hw> <pr>(⟦esl⟧*k⟦icr⟧d"n⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L., a viper, adder, Gr. <grk>'e`chidna</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Gr. Myth.)</fld> <def>A monster, half maid and half
serpent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>A genus of
<ord>Monotremata</ord> found in Australia, Tasmania, and New Guinea.
They are toothless and covered with spines; -- called also
<altname>porcupine ant-eater</altname>, and <altname>Australian
ant-eater</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Echidnine</ent>⟦br⟧
